This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the robustness of neural networks. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it discusses the sensitivity of neural networks to perturbations such as blur and rotations. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial examples. It could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the security of neural networks against adversarial attacks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the robustness of neural networks.
